wiki/Sacred_lotus_in_religious_art" title=3D"Sacred lotus in religious art"=
>lotus flower</a>) in his four hands, and a similar problem for a ten-hande=
d god.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Factorial#cite_note-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>In the mathematics of the Middle East, the Hebrew mystic book of creati=
on <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sefer_Yetzirah" title=3D"Sef=
er Yetzirah">Sefer Yetzirah</a></i>, from the <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Talmud" title=3D"Talmud">Talmudic period</a> (200 to 500&nbsp;C=
E), lists factorials up to 7! as part of an investigation into the number o=
f words that can be formed from the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Hebrew_alphabet" title=3D"Hebrew alphabet">Hebrew alphabet</a>.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-katz_5-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Factorial#cite_note-katz-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Factorial#cite_note-6"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup> Factorials were also studied for similar reasons by 8th-century=
 Arab grammarian <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-Khalil_ibn_Ahm=
ad_al-Farahidi" title=3D"Al-Khalil ibn Ahmad al-Farahidi">Al-Khalil ibn Ahm=
ad al-Farahidi</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-katz_5-1" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Factorial#cite_note-katz-5"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> =
Arab mathematician <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ibn_al-Haytham"=
