tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Factorial#cite_note-31"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>31<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Their use i=
n counting permutations can also be restated algebraically: the factorials =
are the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Order_of_a_group" class=3D=
"mw-redirect" title=3D"Order of a group">orders</a> of finite <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symmetric_group" title=3D"Symmetric group">symm=
etric groups</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-32" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Factorial#cite_note-32"><span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calculus" title=3D"Calculus">calculus</a>=
, factorials occur in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fa%C3%A0_di_=
Bruno%27s_formula" title=3D"Fa=C3=A0 di Bruno's formula">Fa=C3=A0 di Bruno'=
s formula</a> for chaining higher derivatives.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-craik_19-=
1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Factorial#c=
ite_note-craik-19"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>19<span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
